item.title: Hassan Nasrallah to Nabil Kaouk: 7 Hezbollah commanders killed in Israeli strikes in 7 days
item.description: Israel has significantly escalated its actions against Hezbollah by killing seven top commanders, including leader Hassan Nasrallah. This move follows Hezbollah's alliance with Hamas in Gaza. The deaths present a major challenge for the organization. The group's Shura Council is expected to meet soon to select new leadership.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'My crowds are pretty big': Kamala Harris mocks Trump during fundraiser
item.description: Kamala Harris targeted Donald Trump at a fundraiser, boasting about her campaign's large crowds and addressing immigration in key states like Arizona and Nevada. She dismissed Trump's criticisms while gaining support from some Republicans. Harris also promised to eliminate federal taxes on tips for service workers, emphasizing the close race to the White House.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Sean 'Diddy' Combs taken 'off suicide watch' as court trial looms
item.description: Sean "Diddy" Combs is no longer under intensive monitoring at Brooklyn's detention center where he faces sexual assault and prostitution charges. Despite being denied bail twice, including a $50 million offer, Combs remains focused on his legal defense. His family has surrendered their passports to support his claim of not being a flight risk.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Melania Trump reveals her son Barron Trump's living situation in college
item.description: Melania Trump shared that her son Barron is residing at the family's Trump Tower home while attending New York University. She respects his decision to live in New York and hopes he enjoys his college experience. Barron, a recent Oxbridge Academy graduate, is enrolled at NYU's Stern School of Business.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Could an all-out war in the Middle East be avoided? What Biden said
item.description: US President Joe Biden has urged for efforts to prevent an all-out war in the Middle East amid rising tensions between Israel and Hezbollah. Following Israeli airstrikes that killed Hezbollah leader Hassan Nasrallah, Biden expressed worries about potential involvement from Iran and the US. He plans to communicate with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu soon.
item.dc:creator: TOI News Desk

Israel's Netanyahu adds rival to Cabinet, strengthens hold on office
item.description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has expanded his coalition by appointing former rival Gideon Saar to his Cabinet as a minister without portfolio. Saar will also serve in the Security Cabinet. This strategic appointment aims to fortify Netanyahu's position amid significant political challenges, including budget passage and military draft issues, while reducing ultranationalist influence.

item.title: US President Biden to visit Hurricane Helene-affected areas amid ongoing recovery efforts
item.description: President Joe Biden plans to visit areas hit by Hurricane Helene, ensuring it won't disrupt rescue efforts. He assured state officials of continued federal support as the storm's death toll reaches at least 84 across several states. Former President Donald Trump will also visit Georgia for damage assessment and relief distribution.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: War intensifies in Middle East as Israel hit Beirut city for first time, also struck Houthis in Yemen
item.description: An Israeli airstrike targeted an apartment building in Beirut, killing at least two people and heightening regional tensions. This incident follows recent strikes on Hezbollah and Houthi positions. Over 1,000 Lebanese have died recently, with a million displaced. The US is advocating for diplomatic resolutions to avoid further conflict.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Nasa astronauts receive new ride home as SpaceX Dragon capsule arrives at ISS
item.description: Two astronauts stuck on the ISS since June finally got their return transport through a SpaceX capsule after NASA deemed Boeing's Starliner unsafe due to thruster failures and helium leaks. The Dragon capsule will remain docked until February, while NASA continues inspecting the Starliner.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: US couple charged after allegedly attempting to sell baby for $1,000 and six-pack of beer
item.description: An American couple from Arkansas has been arrested for allegedly attempting to sell their two-month-old baby at a campground for $1,000 and a six-pack of beer. The child was found in poor condition and is now under the care of the Arkansas Department of Human Services. The couple faces felony charges.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Zookeeper mauled to death by lion in Nigeria after leaving protective gate open
item.description: Babaji Daule, a zookeeper at the Presidential Library Wildlife Park in Abeokuta, Nigeria, was killed by a lion after leaving the protective gate open during feeding. Authorities intervened and shot the lion to prevent further harm. This marks the second fatal lion attack on a Nigerian zookeeper within a year, raising safety concerns.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'We really have to avoid it': Biden urges avoidance of all-out war as Israel-Hezbollah tensions escalate
item.description: US President Joe Biden highlighted the necessity of preventing an all-out war in the Middle East amid rising tensions between Israel and Hezbollah. Israeli airstrikes in Lebanon resulted in significant casualties, including Hezbollah leader Hassan Nasrallah's death. The White House supports a 21-day temporary cease-fire proposed by multiple nations during the recent UN General Assembly.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Please don't do...': British priest issues a warning to Americans
item.description: Calvin Robinson, a British Anglican catholic priest and conservative commentator, advises Americans to avoid cultural missteps observed in the UK. He criticizes the UK government's handling of recent riots and expresses concern over the Church of England's liberal shift, which he believes weakens traditional Christian values. Robinson urges Americans to maintain their cultural identity.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Nepal's monsoon floods toll reaches 170 as Kathmandu struggles to recover
item.description: Floods in Nepal's capital have left at least 170 dead and thousands displaced. Monsoon rains triggered flash floods and landslides, causing widespread destruction. Rescue efforts have saved over 3,000 people as teams work to clear highways and restore access. Domestic flights have resumed following significant weather-related disruptions.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Neither has earned my vote': Larry Hogan slams Trump and Harris ahead of US presidential elections
item.description: Former Maryland governor Larry Hogan stated he will not vote for Donald Trump or Kamala Harris in the upcoming US presidential election. Running for a Senate seat, Hogan criticized both parties for deviating from their core values and expressed concerns over divisive politics. He also reiterated his past opposition to Trump despite receiving his endorsement.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Who Is Jeff Flake? The conservative Republican Who endorsed Kamala Harris
item.description: Former GOP Senator Jeff Flake has endorsed Vice President Kamala Harris for president, emphasizing the need for leadership focused on future hope rather than past grievances. Known for his opposition to Donald Trump, Flake's endorsement aligns with his history of prioritizing national interests over party loyalty and underscores his conservative values.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: In historic first, Putin-friendly far-right Freedom Party wins Austria elections
item.description: Austria's far-right Freedom Party (FPO), under Herbert Kickl's leadership, has won the general election with 29.1% of the vote. The FPO outpaced Chancellor Karl Nehammer's Austrian People's Party (OVP). The party's focus on immigration and economic issues tapped into public frustration over inflation, the Ukraine war, and migration concerns. Kickl needs a coalition partner to govern.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Former Republican senator Jeff Flake backs Kamala Harris in 2024 US presidential elections
item.description: Republican Jeff Flake endorsed Democratic candidate Kamala Harris for the 2024 US Presidential elections. Having served as US Ambassador to Turkey under Biden, Flake stressed unity and respect for the rule of law. He called on Republicans to prioritize country over party and support candidates who aim to unite rather than divide.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk
